# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: SailorPath | Scene: SailorPath6
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The day had started early for Sarah."
    new "The day had started early for Sarah."

    old "Work on the ship often cycled between long stretches of boredom and peaks of intensity."
    new "Work on the ship often cycled between long stretches of boredom and peaks of intensity."

    old "With their upcoming departure to fulfill captain Belmont's latest contract to deliver crates of coal to the city of Northam, their boredom was long gone."
    new "With their upcoming departure to fulfill captain Belmont's latest contract to deliver crates of coal to the city of Northam, their boredom was long gone."

    old "The list of things to do seemed nearly endless, and with every passing moment, more work seemed to be added."
    new "The list of things to do seemed nearly endless, and with every passing moment, more work seemed to be added."

    old "Sometimes she walked past and the captain would should out more orders, more preparations, more items they needed from the market."
    new "Sometimes she walked past and the captain would should out more orders, more preparations, more items they needed from the market."

    old "It was busy, but to Sarah, it felt like the good kind."
    new "It was busy, but to Sarah, it felt like the good kind."

    old "Hey, stop day dreaming!"
    new "Hey, stop day dreaming!"

    old "Nick's sudden comment startled Sarah."
    new "Nick's sudden comment startled Sarah."

    old "Did you get that copper gear wire from the dock smithy?"
    new "Did you get that copper gear wire from the dock smithy?"

    old "Yeah, I just dropped it off below deck."
    new "Yeah, I just dropped it off below deck."

    old "Alright, we can scratch that off the list."
    new "Alright, we can scratch that off the list."

    old "How about the pressing oil?"
    new "How about the pressing oil?"

    old "I...I didn't get that yet, sorry."
    new "I...I didn't get that yet, sorry."

    old "Nick pulled his hands through his hair, pressing his hair back."
    new "Nick pulled his hands through his hair, pressing his hair back."

    old "Sarah found it hard not to look at how his upper arms bulged whenever he did."
    new "Sarah found it hard not to look at how his upper arms bulged whenever he did."

    old "I think...we're still good. We'll just have to get it before the day is out."
    new "I think...we're still good. We'll just have to get it before the day is out."

    old "Today? When are we gonna get the time? We also have to pick up food stuffs from the butcher, and that's all the way up hill."
    new "Today? When are we gonna get the time? We also have to pick up food stuffs from the butcher, and that's all the way up hill."

    old "Sure, that's true, but the pressing oil store won't be open tomorrow. So we should get that done today."
    new "Sure, that's true, but the pressing oil store won't be open tomorrow. So we should get that done today."

    old "Alright. Do we split up?"
    new "Alright. Do we split up?"

    old "Pressing oil comes in solid bronze cylindrical containers about the size of a small child."
    new "Pressing oil comes in solid bronze cylindrical containers about the size of a small child."

    old "And for a ship this size and the journey, we're talking about three units."
    new "And for a ship this size and the journey, we're talking about three units."

    old "Best we go together."
    new "Best we go together."

    old "Ok, let's go then."
    new "Ok, let's go then."

    old "Sarah began to walk, only to realize she had little idea where the pressing oil business was located."
    new "Sarah began to walk, only to realize she had little idea where the pressing oil business was located."

    old "Uhm...maybe you lead the way?"
    new "Uhm...maybe you lead the way?"

    old "Nick laughed."
    new "Nick laughed."

    old "Sure, just keep up Sarah. We'll have to pick up the pace if we wanna get it all done."
    new "Sure, just keep up Sarah. We'll have to pick up the pace if we wanna get it all done."

    old "Together, Sarah and Nick took off from the docks, deeper into the city."
    new "Together, Sarah and Nick took off from the docks, deeper into the city."

    old "Just as promised, Sarah watched Nick walk in broad strides."
    new "Just as promised, Sarah watched Nick walk in broad strides."

    old "He was taller than Sarah by about a head, and his long legs made his broad steps more akin to running for Sarah."
    new "He was taller than Sarah by about a head, and his long legs made his broad steps more akin to running for Sarah."

    old "Still, she wasn't about to complain. Half running, Sarah did her best to keep up with Nick."
    new "Still, she wasn't about to complain. Half running, Sarah did her best to keep up with Nick."

    old "Nick was strict, but as far as Sarah could tell, he was fair and a willing tutor."
    new "Nick was strict, but as far as Sarah could tell, he was fair and a willing tutor."

    old "He went fast, but he was diligent to explain each step to Sarah."
    new "He went fast, but he was diligent to explain each step to Sarah."

    old "More importantly, not only did he show her each step, he also was careful to explain the why of each step to her."
    new "More importantly, not only did he show her each step, he also was careful to explain the why of each step to her."

    old "Sarah was rapidly beginning to understand the many complexities of rigging and sailing a ship, but also the economy of simply managing a small cargo ship."
    new "Sarah was rapidly beginning to understand the many complexities of rigging and sailing a ship, but also the economy of simply managing a small cargo ship."

    old "It was a lot, but Sarah was eager for the challenge. Finally she had something to put her mind to."
    new "It was a lot, but Sarah was eager for the challenge. Finally she had something to put her mind to."

    old "She skipped a few steps, catching back up to Nick."
    new "She skipped a few steps, catching back up to Nick."

    old "So, you know your way around Rahayal?"
    new "So, you know your way around Rahayal?"

    old "Been here a few times."
    new "Been here a few times."

    old "One time I ended up staying for nearly three months. You end up getting to know a city. Or at least the docks."
    new "One time I ended up staying for nearly three months. You end up getting to know a city. Or at least the docks."

    old "You don't stay anywhere long?"
    new "You don't stay anywhere long?"

    old "Nah. I like to stay on the move, never settle anywhere for long. Sailing is one of the few vocations where that's actually a benefit."
    new "Nah. I like to stay on the move, never settle anywhere for long. Sailing is one of the few vocations where that's actually a benefit."

    old "Don't you miss family?"
    new "Don't you miss family?"

    old "Can't miss what you ain't got."
    new "Can't miss what you ain't got."

    old "Grew up in an orphanage in Lethram. Ran away when I was about thirteen and never looked back."
    new "Grew up in an orphanage in Lethram. Ran away when I was about thirteen and never looked back."

    old "Sarah struggled to wrap her mind around it."
    new "Sarah struggled to wrap her mind around it."

    old "The streets of Lethram seemed dangerous to her at twenty-two, she couldn't imagine trying to survive at thirteen."
    new "The streets of Lethram seemed dangerous to her at twenty-two, she couldn't imagine trying to survive at thirteen."

    old "How could you possibly have survived that?"
    new "How could you possibly have survived that?"

    old "Easy. You work the docks, loading and unloading ships."
    new "Easy. You work the docks, loading and unloading ships."

    old "You do a good job, don't cause trouble, and one of the dock stewards will spot you sooner or later."
    new "You do a good job, don't cause trouble, and one of the dock stewards will spot you sooner or later."

    old "Dock stewards put in a good word for you, and before you know it a captain will let you work on a ship, double the pay."
    new "Dock stewards put in a good word for you, and before you know it a captain will let you work on a ship, double the pay."

    old "Do a good job there, get a few years in, captains will be fightin to get you to work for em."
    new "Do a good job there, get a few years in, captains will be fightin to get you to work for em."

    old "Wow. I never knew it all worked like that."
    new "Wow. I never knew it all worked like that."

    old "Sarah suddenly felt guilty, having so easily skipped years of work to get a job as a deck hand."
    new "Sarah suddenly felt guilty, having so easily skipped years of work to get a job as a deck hand."

    old "How about you? What's your story?"
    new "How about you? What's your story?"

    old "Me? Ooh, I grew up in Rosanna for most of my life."
    new "Me? Ooh, I grew up in Rosanna for most of my life."

    old "Rosanna? Isn't that all across the sea?"
    new "Rosanna? Isn't that all across the sea?"

    old "And didn't something happen over there recently?"
    new "And didn't something happen over there recently?"

    old "Yeah...but...I'd rather not talk about that, if that's alright?"
    new "Yeah...but...I'd rather not talk about that, if that's alright?"

    old "Nick suddenly stopped walking."
    new "Nick suddenly stopped walking."

    old "Ooh...Sarah, I'm sorry. I didn't know, or think that you might have been...I'm so sorry."
    new "Ooh...Sarah, I'm sorry. I didn't know, or think that you might have been...I'm so sorry."

    old "It's alright, I've just been trying not to think about it too much."
    new "It's alright, I've just been trying not to think about it too much."

    old "So I just grew up in Rosanna, then the invasion happened and I managed to escape, but...my family didn't."
    new "So I just grew up in Rosanna, then the invasion happened and I managed to escape, but...my family didn't."

    old "So you're all alone?"
    new "So you're all alone?"

    old "Sarah nodded, turning her eyes to the ground."
    new "Sarah nodded, turning her eyes to the ground."

    old "Pretty much."
    new "Pretty much."

    old "Nick suddenly punched her on the shoulder."
    new "Nick suddenly punched her on the shoulder."

    old "Don't be so gloom. I've been alone most of my life. You've only been alone for a few weeks."
    new "Don't be so gloom. I've been alone most of my life. You've only been alone for a few weeks."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah found herself laughing."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah found herself laughing."

    old "Yeah, I guess that's one way of looking at it."
    new "Yeah, I guess that's one way of looking at it."

    old "They started to walk again."
    new "They started to walk again."

    old "Sorry for asking though. I like to get to know people I work with, but I forget sometimes people got a story they prefer to keep to themselves."
    new "Sorry for asking though. I like to get to know people I work with, but I forget sometimes people got a story they prefer to keep to themselves."

    old "It's ok."
    new "It's ok."

    old "I like talking to people. I like talking to you."
    new "I like talking to people. I like talking to you."

    old "Yeah? Doesn't our captain make for a good conversationalist?"
    new "Yeah? Doesn't our captain make for a good conversationalist?"

    old "No, he's not really one for talking. Or at least, I don't think he ever really listens much to what I have to say."
    new "No, he's not really one for talking. Or at least, I don't think he ever really listens much to what I have to say."

    old "I can't blame him. It can be hard to look at you and not get distracted."
    new "I can't blame him. It can be hard to look at you and not get distracted."

    old "He winked at her."
    new "He winked at her."

    old "Sarah could feel her face turn red and forced herself to look forward."
    new "Sarah could feel her face turn red and forced herself to look forward."

    old "I...I mean...yeah...I don't know."
    new "I...I mean...yeah...I don't know."

    old "I'm just messing with you Sarah."
    new "I'm just messing with you Sarah."

    old "Yeah, I know. I guess I'm still just getting the hang of all this, the sailor life I mean."
    new "Yeah, I know. I guess I'm still just getting the hang of all this, the sailor life I mean."

    old "Can't be easy for you, I guess. Given that your family was rich."
    new "Can't be easy for you, I guess. Given that your family was rich."

    old "Sarah suddenly looked at him."
    new "Sarah suddenly looked at him."

    old "What makes you say that? I never told you my family was rich."
    new "What makes you say that? I never told you my family was rich."

    old "Nick smiled."
    new "Nick smiled."

    old "You didn't need to tell me."
    new "You didn't need to tell me."

    old "I've seen you helping the captain with dock paperwork, so you're literate. They don't teach just anyone how to read and write."
    new "I've seen you helping the captain with dock paperwork, so you're literate. They don't teach just anyone how to read and write."

    old "Maybe I just happened to be born into a family that did decide to teach me?"
    new "Maybe I just happened to be born into a family that did decide to teach me?"

    old "I guess that's possible, but then you're hands give you away."
    new "I guess that's possible, but then you're hands give you away."

    old "My hands?"
    new "My hands?"

    old "Yeah. You turn em over and look at your palms."
    new "Yeah. You turn em over and look at your palms."

    old "Barely any calluses on them. You get pretty hands like that by doin just about nothing all your life."
    new "Barely any calluses on them. You get pretty hands like that by doin just about nothing all your life."

    old "Sarah turned her hands back over."
    new "Sarah turned her hands back over."

    old "Whatever. What do you care how rich my family was?"
    new "Whatever. What do you care how rich my family was?"

    old "I don't. Just makin conversation. I thought you liked talking with me?"
    new "I don't. Just makin conversation. I thought you liked talking with me?"

    old "I'm liking it less by the minute."
    new "I'm liking it less by the minute."

    old "That's fair."
    new "That's fair."

    old "Only a moment later, the two found themselves in front of the pressing oil store."
    new "Only a moment later, the two found themselves in front of the pressing oil store."

    old "Nick went in alone and came walking out empty handed."
    new "Nick went in alone and came walking out empty handed."

    old "No pressing oil?"
    new "No pressing oil?"

    old "They got some, but they're still pouring it. Said it will be a few minutes."
    new "They got some, but they're still pouring it. Said it will be a few minutes."

    old "Let's wait over there."
    new "Let's wait over there."

    old "Nick gestured towards a fountain nearby."
    new "Nick gestured towards a fountain nearby."

    old "Together, they sat down on the edge of the fountain. Behind them, statues had been carved out, displaying some historical moment that Sarah couldn't identify."
    new "Together, they sat down on the edge of the fountain. Behind them, statues had been carved out, displaying some historical moment that Sarah couldn't identify."

    old "The flow of the water seemed to ease the weight of the city."
    new "The flow of the water seemed to ease the weight of the city."

    old "It's calming clatter drove out the busy throng of voices, and the circulating water cleaned up the air, making it feel cooler to the touch and less of an oppressive heat."
    new "It's calming clatter drove out the busy throng of voices, and the circulating water cleaned up the air, making it feel cooler to the touch and less of an oppressive heat."

    old "Sarah closed her eyes for a moment. Life didn't seem all that bad here."
    new "Sarah closed her eyes for a moment. Life didn't seem all that bad here."

    old "When she opened them again, she saw Nick staring at her."
    new "When she opened them again, she saw Nick staring at her."

    old "Nothing. Can't a guy watch a pretty girl?"
    new "Nothing. Can't a guy watch a pretty girl?"

    old "Sarah looked away, feeling her face turn red again."
    new "Sarah looked away, feeling her face turn red again."

    old "You're teasing me."
    new "You're teasing me."

    old "Maybe I'm not."
    new "Maybe I'm not."

    old "Don't bully me Nick, please, not you."
    new "Don't bully me Nick, please, not you."

    old "Suddenly, she could feel him grab her hand."
    new "Suddenly, she could feel him grab her hand."

    old "Sarah, I'm not, really."
    new "Sarah, I'm not, really."

    old "Sarah pulled her hand back."
    new "Sarah pulled her hand back."

    old "Dangerous. This was dangerous."
    new "Dangerous. This was dangerous."

    old "You shouldn't do this."
    new "You shouldn't do this."

    old "Why not? Ain't a crime to tell a girl she's pretty."
    new "Why not? Ain't a crime to tell a girl she's pretty."

    old "Maybe not a crime, but you'll get in trouble. You'll get the both of us in trouble."
    new "Maybe not a crime, but you'll get in trouble. You'll get the both of us in trouble."

    old "Trouble with who?"
    new "Trouble with who?"

    old "The captain. He told me to stay away from you."
    new "The captain. He told me to stay away from you."

    old "So what. Does he own you?"
    new "So what. Does he own you?"

    old "No, he doesn't own me."
    new "No, he doesn't own me."

    old "So who cares then?"
    new "So who cares then?"

    old "Nick...he gave me a chance when nobody else did in this world. Gave me a job."
    new "Nick...he gave me a chance when nobody else did in this world. Gave me a job."

    old "If I go and...break his trust...he'll throw me back out onto the street."
    new "If I go and...break his trust...he'll throw me back out onto the street."

    old "Then work for a different captain."
    new "Then work for a different captain."

    old "I'm not like you, Nick. I don't have years of experience. I can't just work for another captain."
    new "I'm not like you, Nick. I don't have years of experience. I can't just work for another captain."

    old "I guess not. It was wrong of me to suggest that it could be that easy."
    new "I guess not. It was wrong of me to suggest that it could be that easy."

    old "So what? You just let him fuck you?"
    new "So what? You just let him fuck you?"

    old "No! I...what are you..."
    new "No! I...what are you..."

    old "I'm not stupid, Sarah."
    new "I'm not stupid, Sarah."

    old "I got to lay in my bunk last night listening to you howl like you'd lost your mind."
    new "I got to lay in my bunk last night listening to you howl like you'd lost your mind."

    old "Sarah felt her face turn red, the rush of blood making it feel like her head was boiling."
    new "Sarah felt her face turn red, the rush of blood making it feel like her head was boiling."

    old "No...Nick...I...."
    new "No...Nick...I...."

    old "Just don't lie to me..."
    new "Just don't lie to me..."

    old "Sarah looked down to the ground, trying to find the words."
    new "Sarah looked down to the ground, trying to find the words."

    old "It's...alright, I won't lie."
    new "It's...alright, I won't lie."

    old "You're right. He and I did...we did have sex."
    new "You're right. He and I did...we did have sex."

    old "She could see from the corner of her eye that Nick was looking directly at her."
    new "She could see from the corner of her eye that Nick was looking directly at her."

    old "But it's not like I...love him, or anything."
    new "But it's not like I...love him, or anything."

    old "It's just...this world is rotten, Nick. Nobody gives anybody something for nothing."
    new "It's just...this world is rotten, Nick. Nobody gives anybody something for nothing."

    old "And I was out on the street with nothing. I had nowhere to go."
    new "And I was out on the street with nothing. I had nowhere to go."

    old "He offered me a way out. A way for me to move up instead of always falling down."
    new "He offered me a way out. A way for me to move up instead of always falling down."

    old "And so, I made a deal with him. He gave me that and...I gave him...the only thing I had."
    new "And so, I made a deal with him. He gave me that and...I gave him...the only thing I had."

    old "Nick was quiet for a moment, before finally speaking."
    new "Nick was quiet for a moment, before finally speaking."

    old "Sarah...I'm sorry if I was harsh."
    new "Sarah...I'm sorry if I was harsh."

    old "It wasn't fair of me to be. You've lived your own life, and had to survive your own way."
    new "It wasn't fair of me to be. You've lived your own life, and had to survive your own way."

    old "It's not up to me to judge you for those choices."
    new "It's not up to me to judge you for those choices."

    old "Sarah felt tears begin to form."
    new "Sarah felt tears begin to form."

    old "He should be disgusted by her. Think she was nothing but a whore."
    new "He should be disgusted by her. Think she was nothing but a whore."

    old "Instead, he offered her kindness."
    new "Instead, he offered her kindness."

    old "Sarah looked up at Nick."
    new "Sarah looked up at Nick."

    old "That face of his, seemingly unmarked by any adversity, beautiful. So beautiful he seemed almost radiant, crowned by his golden blonde hair."
    new "That face of his, seemingly unmarked by any adversity, beautiful. So beautiful he seemed almost radiant, crowned by his golden blonde hair."

    old "Kiss Nick"
    new "Kiss Nick"

    old "Damn it all to hell. She had one life to live and she wasn't gonna waste it living it on the terms of anyone else."
    new "Damn it all to hell. She had one life to live and she wasn't gonna waste it living it on the terms of anyone else."

    old "Sarah leapt forward, and pressed her lips up against Nick's."
    new "Sarah leapt forward, and pressed her lips up against Nick's."

    old "She had caught him by surprise, but she could feel him slowly warm to her."
    new "She had caught him by surprise, but she could feel him slowly warm to her."

    old "His hand gripped her waist, pulling her closer."
    new "His hand gripped her waist, pulling her closer."

    old "With his other hand, he touched the side of her face with a gentleness that Sarah had long not felt."
    new "With his other hand, he touched the side of her face with a gentleness that Sarah had long not felt."

    old "His lips were soft. Rather than a coarse beard, she could feel his skin. And rather than invade her mouth with his tongue as Belmont did, he met her at her speed."
    new "His lips were soft. Rather than a coarse beard, she could feel his skin. And rather than invade her mouth with his tongue as Belmont did, he met her at her speed."

    old "Sarah could feel her heart soar."
    new "Sarah could feel her heart soar."

    old "As she pulled back from him, she could see his kindly smile on his strong face."
    new "As she pulled back from him, she could see his kindly smile on his strong face."

    old "Had she dreamt of a man like this for so often that she had willed him into existence? Sarah struggled to imagine what else might have caused him to be so perfect."
    new "Had she dreamt of a man like this for so often that she had willed him into existence? Sarah struggled to imagine what else might have caused him to be so perfect."

    old "I didn't think you would."
    new "I didn't think you would."

    old "Maybe you don't know me as well as you think."
    new "Maybe you don't know me as well as you think."

    old "I'd like to get to know you then."
    new "I'd like to get to know you then."

    old "Don't kiss Nick"
    new "Don't kiss Nick"

    old "For a fleeting moment, Sarah considered kissing him."
    new "For a fleeting moment, Sarah considered kissing him."

    old "But a voice rang out in her head. Captain Belmont."
    new "But a voice rang out in her head. Captain Belmont."

    old "He had warned her, and Belmont didn't make idle threats."
    new "He had warned her, and Belmont didn't make idle threats."

    old "Nick was handsome, and she even liked him, but she couldn't take this risk for something as silly as a crush."
    new "Nick was handsome, and she even liked him, but she couldn't take this risk for something as silly as a crush."

    old "They sat in silence for a moment."
    new "They sat in silence for a moment."

    old "A voice rang out over the square and a man waved at them both."
    new "A voice rang out over the square and a man waved at them both."

    old "Ooh, that's the store owner, I think the pressing oil is ready."
    new "Ooh, that's the store owner, I think the pressing oil is ready."

    old "Sarah watched Nick walk inside and emerge a moment later, carrying two massive bronze cylinders. One on each shoulder."
    new "Sarah watched Nick walk inside and emerge a moment later, carrying two massive bronze cylinders. One on each shoulder."

    old "There is a third one inside, you pick that one, alright?"
    new "There is a third one inside, you pick that one, alright?"

    old "Sarah was stunned that he could speak so calmly. The weight of the containers seemed almost not to affect him."
    new "Sarah was stunned that he could speak so calmly. The weight of the containers seemed almost not to affect him."

    old "Grabbing her own canister, Sarah nearly felt her back go out."
    new "Grabbing her own canister, Sarah nearly felt her back go out."

    old "Don't complain, be strong, she reminded herself."
    new "Don't complain, be strong, she reminded herself."

    old "With all the strength she could muster, she heaved the great thing unto her shoulders."
    new "With all the strength she could muster, she heaved the great thing unto her shoulders."

    old "Through gritted teeth, she caught up to Nick."
    new "Through gritted teeth, she caught up to Nick."

    old "Don't worry, it gets easier."
    new "Don't worry, it gets easier."

    old "I mean, maybe never as easy as for me, but you'll learn to carry em."
    new "I mean, maybe never as easy as for me, but you'll learn to carry em."

    old "Once your muscles come in."
    new "Once your muscles come in."

    old "Sarah heard him laugh heartedly at his own joke."
    new "Sarah heard him laugh heartedly at his own joke."

    old "You're very funny."
    new "You're very funny."

    old "Slowly, the two made their way down the winding roads, back to the docks."
    new "Slowly, the two made their way down the winding roads, back to the docks."

    old "From a distance, Sarah could already spot captain Belmont, pacing back and forth across the upper deck of the ship."
    new "From a distance, Sarah could already spot captain Belmont, pacing back and forth across the upper deck of the ship."

    old "Together, Sarah and Nick walked up the plank, onto the ship."
    new "Together, Sarah and Nick walked up the plank, onto the ship."

    old "Gods! Where have you two miserable good for nothings been hanging out?"
    new "Gods! Where have you two miserable good for nothings been hanging out?"

    old "Nick put the two canisters down with a heavy thud."
    new "Nick put the two canisters down with a heavy thud."

    old "Pressing oil."
    new "Pressing oil."

    old "Ooh. That's fine then, good, stack it over by the corner there."
    new "Ooh. That's fine then, good, stack it over by the corner there."

    old "Doing as instructed, Nick grabbed the solid bronze canisters back uo and began packing them."
    new "Doing as instructed, Nick grabbed the solid bronze canisters back uo and began packing them."

    old "Sarah added hers to the others."
    new "Sarah added hers to the others."

    old "How we comin on those sails? They need to be test rigged, see if there's any tearing on them. I don't wanna find none when we set out."
    new "How we comin on those sails? They need to be test rigged, see if there's any tearing on them. I don't wanna find none when we set out."

    old "Yes, captain. I was going to do that next, show Sarah how its done."
    new "Yes, captain. I was going to do that next, show Sarah how its done."

    old "Belmont waved his hand at Nick, dismissing him."
    new "Belmont waved his hand at Nick, dismissing him."

    old "Yes, fine. Just get it done. Got too much stress already."
    new "Yes, fine. Just get it done. Got too much stress already."

    old "Sarah walked over to Nick, happy to escape much of the captain's anger for the day."
    new "Sarah walked over to Nick, happy to escape much of the captain's anger for the day."

    old "Near to the front of the ship, close to the cables, they were far enough for Belmont not to be able to hear them."
    new "Near to the front of the ship, close to the cables, they were far enough for Belmont not to be able to hear them."

